  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of present study is to to investigate whether the combined injection of HA and CS was
      superior than HA alone in the treatment of knee OA.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Intra-articular injection of hyaluronic acid (HA) or corticosteroids (CS) has been widely
      used with debate on its efficacy in osteoarthritis (OA). The aim of present study is to to
      investigate whether the combined injection of HA and CS is superior than HA alone in the
      treatment of knee OA.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
